						  Message:<br><textarea name="msg"  cols="50" rows="20">Check for your bug in here first. Threads about these bugs WILL be closed =) thanks!

Feel free to add replies to this on things you see as common bugs that people come here for. they may or may not be bugs but still may belong on this list! ;)

If you have a serious or private bug, feel free to contact me on IRC (i'll usually be an OP in #archspace) or PREFERABLLY an email to briankearney AT gmail DOT com with &quot;ARCHSPACE&quot; somewhere in the title ;/

------------------
Firefox/Mozilla

I can not drag and drop my ships when deploying my fleets or making a generic defence plan.

Try using the &quot;Java Applet (New)&quot; choice instead of &quot;Java Script (Classic)&quot;
------------------
All Browsers

When setting defense plans with the 'Java' preference it doesn't load?


You need a newer version of the java plugin. Visit http://www.java.com/ or directly http://java.sun.com/webapps/getjava/BrowserRedirect?locale=en&amp;host=www.java.com:80
Follow the instructions to install it and then the applet(s) should work.
------------------
My expeditions take hours and hours or even forever!

This is how they work. They are based on chance and the amount of planets you have from each cluster. It's not a bug, just a feature. Might I suggest attacking people if expeditions begin to take too long and you feel the need for more planets?

------------------
The frames in AS keep disapearing

Just close out your browser and log back into AS. This should fix it.

Note: You probably only need to close the windows that have AS in them and open a new window.  Closing them all isn't neccessary.  Though this should be done if it still dosn't work.

-------------------
Council Forum Bug

During the reset the council forums were not cleared so people can see all posts made there the previouse set.  Please do not report this as the devs are fully aware of it and are working to correct the problem.

Edit added by LordBen 1/2/2005

------------------
A rollback has occured, a time warp has occured, things that I did like buy projects invest etc aren't there.  

All of these are the same bug.  They do not have to be reported.  Belive me all the people in the irc chat let the devs know as soon as they happen.  The rollback is caused by server instability.  In any case don't report these things.

EDIT ADDED BY LordBen
2/10/2005

-------------------
Problem: &quot;I get a white screen whenever I log in&quot;
Answer:  
      go here:
http://www.archspace.org/game_logout.phtml

then log back in.

